cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper proposes a method for neural sequence labeling in natural language processing, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The method involves the use of conditional random fields (CRFs) and semi-Markov models, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of word-level and segment-level information, which could potentially involve computer vision techniques (cs.CV). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on the CoNLL 2003 named entity recognition (NER) shared task, which falls under the category of natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.NE).
